
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gettext` baraye tarjomeh kardan matn-ha (text) dar barname-ha (programs) be zaban-haye mokhtalef (different languages) estefade mishavad. Yani, komak mikonad barname-haye shoma be zaban-haye digar ham kar konand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gettext "matn"`  --> 💬 Chap kardan (print) tarjomeh shodeh (translated) matn  
    🔹 `gettext -s "matn"` --> 📝 Behtarine agar matn shoma dorosht (plural) bashad.
    🔹 `gettext -d domain "matn"`  --> 🏢 Estefade az file tarjomeh (translation file) ba name 'domain'.
    🔹 `gettext -n`  --> 🌍 Tarjomeh bar asase adade morede nazar

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gettext "Hello, world!"

    🔹 Agar tarjomeh "Hello, world!" dar dastras bashad, on ra chap mikonad.

    $ gettext -d myprogram "Good morning"

    🔹 Az file tarjomeh (translation file) baraye barnameh 'myprogram' estefade mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gettext "Welcome to my application."

    🔹 Agar shoma file zaban farsi dashte bashid, mesle "Khosh amadid be barnameh man" namayesh dade mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gettext` command is used to translate text in programs to different languages. It helps your programs work in multiple languages.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gettext "text"`  --> 💬 Print the translated text
    🔹 `gettext -s "text"` --> 📝 Best used for translating plural forms.
    🔹 `gettext -d domain "text"`  --> 🏢 Use a translation file named 'domain'.
    🔹 `gettext -n`  --> 🌍 Translate based on number

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gettext "Hello, world!"

    🔹 If a translation for "Hello, world!" is available, it will print it.

    $ gettext -d myprogram "Good morning"

    🔹 Use the translation file for the program 'myprogram'.

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ gettext "Welcome to my application."

    🔹 If you have a Persian language file, it will display something like "Khosh amadid be barnameh man."
